            <p class="text-justify">Air France is a France-based airline headquartered in Tremblay-en-France. The airline serves 36 destinations in France and operates worldwide scheduled passenger and cargo services to 175 destinations in 78 countries (93 including overseas departments and territories of France). Air France is known for its in-flight catering, in-flight entertainment, le salon, etc. </p>
            <p class="text-justify">If you have plans to book flight tickets from Air France, make sure you check the ongoing offers and deals, <a href="https://www.faresmatch.com/">flight booking</a>, and <a href="https://www.faresmatch.com/cancellation-policy.aspx">cancellation policy</a>. For your ease, below is an overview of Air France’s cancellation policy. </p>
            <h2>Cancellation policy </h2>
            <p class="text-justify">According to <a href="https://www.faresmatch.com/air-france-cancellation-policy.aspx">Air France’s cancellation policy</a>, you can cancel a flight ticket within 24 hours of booking at least 7 days before departure without paying any cancellation fee. However, if you cross the time limitation of 24 hours, you will have to pay the cancellation fee. Also, you can change your flight or travel date without any penalty. </p>
            If the airline cancels your flight, it can either offer you a refund of your full ticket price or re-route you to the next available flight. If you aren’t comfortable with the new flight, you can opt for a refund. </p>
            <h3>Refund policy </h3>
            <p class="text-justify">You can cancel a flight ticket within 24 hours of booking without paying any cancellation fee if you completed the purchase 7 days or more before the initially scheduled departure flight. Before you apply for the refund make sure that the ticket is refundable. In the case of a non-refundable ticket, you may opt for a travel voucher that you may use later. </p>
            <h4>Frequently asked question</h4>
            <h3 class="text-justify">How to cancel a flight ticket with Air France? </h3>
            <p class="text-justify">You can call the Air France customer care office and inform them about the cancellation. Also, you can visit the official website of the airlines and cancel your flight ticket. </p>
            <h3 class="text-justify">How can I make the request for a refund? By when can I expect it? </h3>
            <p class="text-justify">You can visit the official website of Air France and make a request for a refund or you can call customer care. The airline will process the refund within 7 to 20 business days. </p>
            <h3 class="text-justify">Can I ask for compensation if my flight gets delayed by 2 hours? </h3>
            <p class="text-justify">There can be a possibility that your replacement flight delays your arrival by 2 or more hours or your flight was canceled less than 14 days before departure, you are eligible to get compensation. </p>
            <h3 class="text-justify">How to check if my flight is refundable? </h3>
            <p class="text-justify">Though such information is mentioned on the ticket, you can check if your flight is refundable by visiting the official website of the airline and entering the ticket or document number. The Air France website will display refund eligibility and information. </p>

